  "title": "Coffee and Conversation on Bonadan",
  "summary": "In the bustling, ESPO-patrolled Bonadan spaceport, Zeak Oppenhiemer waits over a cup of stim caf for his hired pilot Jaspar to return from a reconnaissance run. Jaspar reports that he ran the Imperial blockade to Caspar and back exactly as planned, name-dropping Zeak's group, getting scanned but cleared, and confirming that traffic control under the Star Destroyer Nemesis explicitly called the system 'under blockade by order of the Emperor.' Jaspar produces the cargo Zeak requested, a squeaky Thel doll from a load of Imperial figurines, to Zeak's ironic amusement. Satisfied with the intelligence, Zeak pays Jaspar with a credit-stuffed envelope plus a gratuity for his passage home, and the two part with mutual hopes of future business.",
